title: For Sale/Trade:  Chilean Mauser 1895 Loewe Berlin Contract Model (7mm Mauser)
postcontent: Up for sale or trade, I have a Chilean Mauser manufactured in 1895. It was a contract model made by Ludwig Loewe/DWM (Deutsche Waffen und Munitionsfabriken), in Berlin. The stock is from 1887. It is the first major modification of the Mauser Model 1893. The Model 1895 was also deployed to republic of the Orange Free State and the South African Republic, aside from it's main use by the Chilean Army. It features a surprisingly crisp bolt and trigger and fires a very capable round that was popular with elephant hunters. The rifle is 121 years old. The magazine floorplate is jammed shut and I have left it that way to avoid causing any harm to the integrity of the rifle. Email, or text me with any offers or questions.

title: For Sale:  Like New LWRC REPR 20" Barrel. Black with less than 80 rounds.
postcontent: The LWRC R.E.P.R or "Rapid Engagement Precision Rifle".  I put less than 100 rounds through this rifle, I got it sighted in and ran it through it paces suppressed and non suppressed.  It never missed a beat.  The piston driven operation keeps the Nickle Boron Bolt Carrier Group very clean!  The action is butter smooth and it makes you understand the build quality that goes into these rifles.  The barrel is cold hammer forged and has an 1:10 twist.  According to LWRC the barrel is rated to 10,000 rounds.  LWRC also added Magpul components with the PRS stock with adjustable cheek piece and length of pull adjustment.  The piston driven operation is extremely reliable and has 4 distinct adjustments, "suppressed, normal, adverse, and off.  Shooting suppressed this Rifle is a dream to shoot.  No gas blowback at all.  It has turned into a "safe queen" since I got into .300 Blackout.   I hate to sell it but I need to fund another project.
